10 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
11 An Act relating to medication; defining term;
directing the Oklahoma Health Care Authority to
12 partner with the University of Oklahoma Health and
Sciences Center to provide medication to certain
13 inmates; directing the Oklahoma Health Care Authority
to directly pay the University of Oklahoma Health and
14 Sciences Center for medication for certain inmates;
providing for promulgation of rules; providing for
15 codification; and providing an effective date.
16
17
18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
19 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
20 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 7500 of Title 63, unless there
21 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
22 A. As used in this section, "medication" means prescription and
23 over-the-counter drugs.
24
HB2059 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 B. The Oklahoma Health Care Authority shall partner with the
2 University of Oklahoma Health and Sciences Center to provide
3 medication to detainees and inmates under the jurisdiction of a
4 municipality or county, and not under the jurisdiction of the
5 Department of Corrections.
6 The Oklahoma Health Care Authority shall directly pay to the
7 University of Oklahoma Health and Sciences Center for medication
8 provided to detainees and inmates under the jurisdiction of a
9 municipality or county, not under the jurisdiction of the Department
10 of Corrections.
11 C. The Oklahoma Health Care Authority shall promulgate rules to
12 implement this section of law.
13 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
14
15 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON APPROPRIATIONS AND BUDGET, dated
03/05/2026 - DO PASS, As Amended and Coauthored.
